      },
      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(?:client_secret|clientSecret|CLIENT_SECRET|webex_client_secret|webexClientSecret|WEBEX_CLIENT_SECRET)[\"'\\s]*[:=][\"'\\s]*([A-Za-z0-9+/=_-]{32,128})\\b",
        "message": "Webex OAuth client secret detected in variable assignment. Client secrets are confidential credentials used to authenticate Webex OAuth applications during token exchange. Exposing client secrets allows unauthorized parties to impersonate your application, access user data, and perform actions on behalf of your integration. Store client secrets securely using environment variables or secure credential management systems.",
