        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(?:refresh_token|refreshToken|REFRESH_TOKEN|webex_refresh_token|webexRefreshToken|WEBEX_REFRESH_TOKEN)[\"'\\s]*[:=][\"'\\s]*([A-Za-z0-9+/=_-]{50,300})",
        "message": "Webex OAuth refresh token detected in variable assignment. Refresh tokens are long-lived credentials used to obtain new access tokens without user re-authentication. These tokens provide persistent access to Webex APIs and user accounts. Exposing refresh tokens allows long-term unauthorized access and account compromise. Store refresh tokens with the highest security measures and implement secure rotation policies.",
