        "message": "Webex OAuth authorization code detected in source code. Authorization codes are temporary credentials obtained during OAuth flow to exchange for access tokens. While short-lived (typically 10 minutes), exposing authorization codes can allow unauthorized token acquisition and account access. Authorization codes should only be used server-side and never logged or stored in client-side code. Implement secure OAuth flow practices.",
